### MANUAL BRANCH CREATION TEST
### Copy and paste each request individually into your HTTP client

@baseUrl = https://kaytop-production.up.railway.app

### 1. LOGIN FIRST - Copy the access_token from response
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@kaytop.com",
  "password": "Admin123"
}

### 2. REPLACE TOKEN BELOW with actual token from step 1
### Example: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

### 3. GET EXISTING BRANCHES (baseline)
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/branches
Authorization: Bearer REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### 4. CREATE TEST BRANCH
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/branches
Authorization: Bearer REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "API Documentation Test Branch",
  "code": "ADTB001",
  "address": "123 Documentation Street, Test Area",
  "state": "Lagos",
  "region": "Lagos State",
  "phone": "08012345678",
  "email": "testbranch@kaytop.com"
}

### 5. VERIFY CREATION
GET {{baseUrl}}/admin/branches
Authorization: Bearer REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

### INSTRUCTIONS:
### 1. Run step 1 in your HTTP client (VS Code REST Client, Postman, etc.)
### 2. Copy the "access_token" value from the response
### 3. Replace "REPLACE_WITH_ACTUAL_TOKEN" with the actual token in steps 3-5
### 4. Run each step and document the responses
### 5. Pay attention to:
###    - HTTP status codes
###    - Response structure
###    - Field names and types
###    - Error messages (if any)
###    - Generated IDs and timestamps